I will pay you a bounty for the tip!  I am a WI CCW holder based out of Green Bay, have worked for a local FFL and remain a consultant with the retailer, and own numerous collector AK's...  My knowledge and experience on the platform is significant, so plesae don't waste my time with clearly overpriced rifles/pistols which are readily available on the retail market.  Also not interested in any rifles/pistols which have been modified from its original configuration, unless the mods are not permanent, the original parts come with the firearm, and I won't be charged for the additional aftermarket parts (feel free to have them removed if want to keep them).Here is a list of some of the things I would be interested in hearing about, but the list is not exclusive and I would be happy to hear from you if the tip is right!*Anything Chrome or Nickel Plated - including AK accessories and replacement parts*Any cutaway / training / school models - would also consider any cutaway rifle/pistol which are non-AK (all cutaways fascinate me)*Rare AK's, such as:   -Egyptian Maadi    -Norinco/Polytech firearms   -Anything Milled (NO US Made firearms, like the Century Centurion 39 or DDI products)   -Any AK's in unusual or rare calibers (ie. .22lr, 9mm, .223/5.56)   -Anything pre-ban (1989 or earlier) which is not in a sporter configuration (has pistol grip)    -Polish made   -Hungarian made   -Iraqi made   -Finnish made   -Isreali made   -German Made   -Bulgarian Made (no recently produced Arsenal rifles/pistols...  I already own most of them!)         -Would be interested in any Arsenal SGL models or rifles imported by Legion   -Any other countries where AK's have been imported from (other than most Romanian firearms - again, already own most of them!)If you know of something I might be interested in hearing about, please email me via the "Contact Seller" button.  Due to my open-ended inquiry, I won't be providing my personal email address or phone number in the listing to reduce the amount of spam/bad tips I am sure to get :)  When contacting me, please provide the following - your source can remain a secret until we can work out payment agreements :)Manufacturer:Importer:Model #:Caliber:Asking Price:Price Negotiable?:Thanks for looking and I look forward to hearing from you!  Take care and stay safe :)

postcontent: VEPR AK47 Rifle .308 The semi-auto hunting rifles VEPR are designed for medium-sized and big games. AK-based design and construction of the rifles provides a reliable operation of parts and mechanisms as well as high-grade shooting in various weather and climatic conditions. The rifles can be used in a wide temperature range (from -50 F up to +120 F). VEPR's parts are manufactured using the same equipment as the very well known lightweight machinegun RPK. A chrome-lined barrel with chrome-lined chamber and bore along with walnut stocks make these rifles very different from other AK-based rifles available in the US market The rifles come with adjustable open sighting devices and a rail for a scope mount attached to the left side of the receiver. postcontent: Our Guardian has proven so popular due to its concealable profile and Commander-length slide that we took it a step further with the CCO – the Concealed Carry Officer – a Commander slide on an Officer frame. The CCO uses a medium-length trigger to facilitate faster draws and better fit in the hand. The gun is rounded out with our stippled shadow grips. Like all Dan Wesson models, this gun is both beautiful and functional.
